storyInfo: One year ago, in a Sarkaz-occupied factory, prior to the changing of the flag, Feist decided to leave the factory and join the Self-Salvation Corps, leading to a clash with Granny Catherine.

attributes.content: One Year Ago...
4:56 P.M. \ Overcast
Munitions Factory No. 11, Highbury District of Londinium

attributes.name: Londinium Worker
attributes.content: Oi, has the last batch of polymer prep come in yet?

attributes.name: Londinium Worker
attributes.content: Whatâ€”what do you mean it hasn't?!
This takes the piss...
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: Who was in charge of transporting those materials?
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: It was, er, the one in charge, er...
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: What are you dithering for?
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: ...It was Feist.
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: That boy...
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: He went out first thing this morning. Should've been back ages ago.
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: Who went with him?
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Tommy, Patto and Day.
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: They're not the same workshop. How'd they get on the same shift?
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: They all get along like a housefire. Keep mucking together all the time. Feist's their little ringleader.
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: You've hit a snag, from the sounds of it.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary

attributes.content: Small potatoes, nothing more.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Small potatoes.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary

attributes.content: Catherine, you know what day it is today, right?
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary

attributes.content: How could I forget?
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: `I've been fearing for my life I'll upset our officer if I sign and it looks like fowl scratch. I started practicing my signature ten whole days ago.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: That's practice under your belt, then. The General's stressing importance hard on the handover ceremony in two days. Reportedly, the Defense Forces' head is showing too.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary

attributes.content: Want a cig?
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: ...Heh. Pass one here.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary

attributes.content: You know why it is all your factory's people have stuck around until now, don't you?
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary

attributes.content: We work very hard.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: That's a given.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary

attributes.content: You do your work very well. We're alike in that regard. Work, get paid, scrape a living.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary

attributes.content: But our employers know all too well the more exceptional a merc's work, the less he can be trusted.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary

attributes.content: Standard fare.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Old manager of this industrial park, Sir Humphrey, never trusted us either. Before you dragged him away.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Don't make trouble for me, Catherine.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary

attributes.content: The mercenary's tone is placid, like he's the one asking Catherine if she wants a smoke. As he so often does.
This is his job. Offing a few disobedient Londinium workers to him is almost the same as the screws she tightens on the daily.
Catherine taps her cigarette into a bag. Can't have ash falling into the machinery.
I've told you more times than I can count.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: If you want efficiency maintained, our factory can't afford one fewer worker.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: I admire you a fair bit, Catherine. Even a typical merc might not even have the guts you do.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary

attributes.content: You've got the stuff. Thing is, it's possible to take anything too far.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary

attributes.content: Londinium's got over a hundred munitions factories just like yours. Even if this whole place was dead empty, the Regent wouldn't care.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary

attributes.content: Nothing will change. The ceremony will come the day after, we'll hand over everything promised, and all our workers will be there.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: No need for you lot to worry about a thing.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: I'll take your word for it, then.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary

attributes.content: Of course. Not got a lighter? You're just holding your cig there...
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: You hold onto it, after all. Londinium smokes always have a sort of engine oil to them. Can't ever get over it.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary

attributes.content: Catherine, what do we do?
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: (Pinches cigarette out)
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: ...Off to the loading area.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Patto! Done there?
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Just this screw left!
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: Sort it out. If this keeps up, they'll be waiting a whole week at least to get more polymer prep.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Polymer up to our ears, it's just batch after batch coming in. The hell are the Sarkaz building?
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: I haven't seen. Granny doesn't let me anywhere near the assembly line. Only her most trusted workmates get to climb up that walkway.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: The longer this keeps up, the more it must be very important to the Sarkaz.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Gotta be a weapon, right? We've been pumping out auto-crossbows for the Sarkaz the last few days in the workshop.
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: Could only be. Still got so many ducal armies outside eyeing us.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Be ghastly letting the Sarkaz get away with this, I tell you.
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: We've got to stop them, Patto. We can't be helping the Sarkaz fend off our own.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Think it'd be any use if we destroyed this batch of prep? Think we'd get sentenced?
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: I'll step up if that's what it comes to. I'm not afraid of being taken in.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: You can't do that.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: ...Granny?
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Grab 'em.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Pattoâ€”do it!
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Ehâ€”?
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: On the fly, she grabs a small file and throws it.
With a clang, the worker's spanner flies out of his hand and onto the ground.
Ugh...
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Do you know what it is you're doing?
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: I'm stopping the Sarkaz!
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: You're making a scene.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: I've got it all planned! It won't drag any of you in. I'll tell the Sarkaz I did it, and thenâ€”
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: â€”and then you'll die at the Sarkaz's hands. You're making yourself out as a hero, aren't you?
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: I'll try and flee. I've been planning this foreverâ€”
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: You're using the crawler you modified. You're hiding on the cargo track, and slipping out of Highbury that way.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: So you knew...
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: I've been living in this industrial park for over fifty years. Whatever silly business you try, it won't slip by me.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Granny, listen to me.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: I received some news. There's a rebel organization active in Sudean right now. They've rescued a whole number of people from the Sarkaz, and they've even taken back some plates!
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: They call themselves the Londinium Citizens' Self-Salvation Corpsâ€”we're going to meet them!
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Are you now?
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: And then?
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Er... what?
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Are they lacking for smiths? Are you going to assemble and automate production pipelines for them, maybe design the next generation of crawlers?
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: You can't even put a single armament together. You're going to go up to the people at this Self-Salvation Corps and tell them you want to bash Sarkaz heads in with spanners?
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: I'm learning!
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: I know the stories you've told me, like how you got selected to build steam armor when you were young, and I've heard you spending night after night polishing at power conduits.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: I don't get it... We're Londinium workers, you've been teaching me that since I was little. You've told me how our factory built modern Victoriaâ€”
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: But now? We're lowering our flag at a handover ceremony, and raising the Sarkaz ensign.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: And then? We're taking the assembly line we're so proud of and producing weapons for the Sarkaz with it, and those weapons will end up pointed at Victorians!
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: How can you bear life like this?
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Like what?
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Life like this is our life, the life you and your parents have always been living.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Look at this factory.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Nobles with titles longer than their surnames, business tossers with lives built on trade, even the Sarkaz... we've had people posing as its master come and go.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: But the assembly line's still there. The machines still haven't come to a halt. Each rivet that's passed through our hands is still in the place it's meant to be.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Whoever might be occupying that palace in the middle of Londinium, this city we built will still see tomorrow and the day after that.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: But I don't want a tomorrow like this!
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: What kind of life is a life without freedom? It's being alive at most, that's it.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: If this factory... if Londinium isn't ours any longer, then what was the point of everything we made for it?!
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: You know, Feist...
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Twenty-five years ago, that night when the flames lit up the sky, your dad said much the same thing to me.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Boss, the Sarkaz are almost backâ€”
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: You're free to go wherever you want.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: But from this moment on, you are forbidden from ever setting foot in the factory again, Feist.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: A worker who won't finish the job with his own hands isn't fit for the job.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Anyone who wants to go with him, I won't stop you either.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Just rememberâ€”you step out of this door, and you are no longer one of us.
attributes.name: Catherine
